The paper discusses attacks and countermeasures in fingerprint-based biometric cryptosystems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of minutiae-based features in the fuzzy vault scheme, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also proposes the use of randomized decoding procedures, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the use of multibiometric cryptosystems, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
